pyspark.sql.functions.negate

Returns the negative value.

Parameters
col : Column or str
      column to calculate negative value for.

Returns : Column
      negative value.

Examples

spark.range(3).select(negative("id")).show()
+------------+
|negative(id)|
+------------+
|           0|
|          -1|
|          -2|
+------------+

